son Irvine]]\n|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|Loan<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County: Three players sign on deadline day|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29018345|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 September 2014|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|27 September 2014\n|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Lewis Toshney]]\n|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|Free<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County: Lewis Toshney impact hailed after first league win|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29396506|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 September 2014|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|9 October 2014\n|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Martin Woods]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]]\n|Free<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County sign up midfielder Martin Woods|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29557834|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 October 2014|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|16 October 2014\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Terry Dunfield]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Oldham Athletic F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]\n|Free<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County: Boss Jim McIntyre grateful for backing from board|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29649673|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 October 2014|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|16 October 2014\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jamie Reckord]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]\n|Free<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County: Boss Jim McIntyre grateful for backing from board|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29649673|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 October 2014|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|2 January 2015\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Craig Curran]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Nuneaton Town F.C.|Nuneaton Town]]\n|Free<ref>{{cite news |title=Ross County: Striker Craig Curran wins six-month contract|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30658578|publisher=BBC Sport|date=2 January 2015|accessdate=11 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|15 January 2015\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Cameron Burgess]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Fulham